fuzz_filename_stat: hang during metadata iteration. Discovered on a
30-second smoke run of the metadata harness. Input is 397 bytes and
contains nested "Rar!\x1a\x07\x01\x00" magic plus a long run of 0x80
/ 0x03 bytes, suggesting the RAR5 extra-field walker or a filename
decode step enters a bounded-but-expensive loop. Likely shares a
root cause with fuzz_open_mem_hang_5e69ffd712.
